k name <i>Alexandros</i>, from <i>alexein</i> ‘to defend’ + <i>anēr</i> ‘man, warrior’ (genitive <i>andros</i>). The name became extremely popular in the post-classical period, and was borne by several individuals in the New Testament and some early Christian saints. Its use as a common given name throughout Europe, however, derives largely from the fame of  Alexander the Great , King of Macedon (  356–323  bc  ), around whom a large body of popular legend grew up in late antiquity, much of which came to be embodied in the medieval ‘Alexander romances’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs Alexander Gordon had at least 1 son with Sir Alexander 3rd Laird Of Stitchill Gordon Of Stitchill."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1375–1412":"1375–1412","1400–1445":"1400–1445","–Female":"Surnud","1445":"1445","1412":"1412","1400":"1400","1375":"1375","Bas, Haute-Loire, Auvergne, France":"Bas, Haute-Loire, Auvergne, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1375–1412":"1375–1412","1400–1445":"1400–1445","–Female":"Kuollut","1445":"1445","1412":"1412","1400":"1400","1375":"1375","Bas, Haute-Loire, Auvergne, France":"Bas, Haute-Loire, Auvergne, Ranska"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée","1375–1412":"1375–1412","1400–1445":"1400–1445","–Female":"Décédée","1445":"1445","1412":"1412","1400":"1400","1375":"1375","Bas, Haute-Loire, Auvergne, France":"Bas, Haute-Loire, Auvergne, France","lifeSummary":"Mrs Alexander Gordon a eu au moins 1 fils avec Sir Alexander 3rd Laird Of Stitchill Gordon Of Stitchill."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","1375–1412":"1375–1412","1400–1445":"1400–1445","–Female":"Verstorben","1445":"1445","1412":"1412","1400":"1400","1375":"1375","Bas, Haute-Loire, Auvergne, France":"Bas, Haute-Loire, Auvergne, Frankreich","lifeSummary":"Mrs Alexander Gordon hatte mit Sir Alexander 3rd Laird Of Stitchill Gordon Of Stitchill mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"–":"Desede","1375–1412":"1375–1412","1400–1445":"1400–1445","–Female":"Desede","1445":"1445","1412":"1412","1400":"1400","1375":"1375","Bas, Haute-Loire, Auvergne